The daily payment limit is 3,000 DKK for users who identify themselves with their CPR number in MobilePay, and 10,000 DKK for users who identify themselves with NemID. All amounts received by the association through MobilePay are deposited into a collection account and transferred to the association's bank account. MobilePay charges a fee of 1% of the transaction amount, with a minimum of 1.00 DKK and a maximum of 2.75 DKK. The association can only link a bank account that is owned by the association itself. Before payments can be transferred to the bank account linked to the solution, the association's ownership of the bank account must be verified by the association's financial institution. Afterward, all payments will be transferred to the registered bank account within 6-8 days. Within five days of completing a payment, it is possible to refund the amount to a member who has changed their mind about their MobilePay Subscription payment. However, this requires that the association sends a request to contact@minforening.dk within the five-day period. As an administrator in MinForening, you have the authority to create an association agreement with MinForening. You only need to approve the above conditions and provide the association's account information. The association agreement entered into with MinForening can be accessed by other administrators in your association under Settings.
